This course gives a thorough introduction to selected theories of linguistics. The course will focus on one or more theories or compare a range of different theories. The teaching consists of readings, seminars and guest lectures.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of the state of the art in theories and methods in the context of Estonian and world linguistics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course the students are able to place their research in the diversity of linguistic theories and methods. The students will be given the possibility to deepen their understanding of selected theories and methods and apply these to concrete linguistic data.
